  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance documents the simulation credibility evidence for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to support evaluation of worst-case operating conditions for centrifugal blood pumps used in cardiopulmonary bypass. A full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 2, with 7 factors formally assessed and 6 scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. All assessed factors meet or exceed required credibility gradations. This package conforms to the Minimal profile; intended-use scope details are documented separately in the sponsor's design history file.",
