      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (normalized index of hemolysis, scalar shear stress distribution) directly linked to device safety endpoint.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and area-weighted mean scalar shear stress are the primary QoIs. Both are directly correlated with red blood cell damage and are accepted surrogates for hemolytic potential in CPB devices per FDA guidance. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
